# Light Enterprise Design Standard V1

Read **[AIPIFY_DESIGN_STANDARD_V1_LIGHT_ENTERPRISE.md](../../AIPIFY_DESIGN_STANDARD_V1_LIGHT_ENTERPRISE.md)** before UI, theme, navigation, Companion visual, or dashboard styling.

Extends [ENTERPRISE_DESIGN_COMMUNICATION_STANDARD.md](../../ENTERPRISE_DESIGN_COMMUNICATION_STANDARD.md) with **visual** direction.

## Default theme

**Light Enterprise Theme** — not dark-mode-first. Warm off-white canvas (`#F7F6F3`), not pure `#FFFFFF` page backgrounds.

## Colors

- **Companion Purple** `#7C3AED` — brand, primary actions, active navigation
- **Soft Blue-Purple** `#6366F1` — links, charts, selected states
- **Dark slate** text · **muted gray** secondary text
- Cards/surfaces: white on warm canvas

Use CSS tokens in `app/globals.css` and `lib/design/light-enterprise-theme.ts` (`AipifyShellClasses`, `AipifyNavClasses`).

## Navigation

Solid Companion Purple for active items — **avoid heavy gradients**. Professional, organized, enterprise-ready.

## Status

Icon + text always — use `AipifyStatusBadge` / `getAipifyStatusPresentation()`. Never color alone.

## Avoid

Gaming · cyberpunk · neon · black-first dashboards · excessive gradients · visual clutter

## Filter

Clarity over effects · professionalism over trends · enterprise quality over noise

